@namespace TTT.UI

<root>
	<text class="h1">How To Play</text>
	<text>
		TTT is a social deduction mode. Most players are Innocents, a few are Traitors, and occasionally a Detective helps the Innocent team with special equipment.
	</text>

	<text class="h1">Role Goals</text>
	<text><strong>Innocent:</strong> survive, gather information, and identify suspicious behavior.</text>
	<text><strong>Detective:</strong> lead investigations, confirm bodies, and use your utility carefully.</text>
	<text><strong>Traitor:</strong> eliminate the Innocent team without exposing yourself too early.</text>

	<text class="h1">Core Flow</text>
	<text>Stick with the group early, but pay attention to who disappears, who lies, and who is found near bodies.</text>
	<text>When you find a corpse, search it for role and death information. Detectives can also collect DNA from identified bodies.</text>
	<text>If your server allows body hanging, you can carry and hang corpses with Hands to create bait or confusion.</text>

	<text class="h1">Karma And RDM</text>
	<text>Randomly damaging or killing teammates will hurt your karma. Low karma reduces your damage and movement speed, and very low karma can get you kicked.</text>
	<text>If you are killed unfairly, use the spectator RDM prompt to file a report. The Global Tribunal page is for voting on open cases.</text>

	<text class="h1">Important Keys</text>
	<div><text>Use / Search:</text><inputglyph action=@InputAction.Use /></div>
	<div><text>Walk:</text><inputglyph action=@InputAction.Run /></div>
	<div><text>Voice Chat:</text><inputglyph action=@InputAction.Voice /></div>
	<div><text>Quick Shop / Role Menu:</text><inputglyph action=@InputAction.View /></div>
	<div><text>Scoreboard / Menu:</text><inputglyph action=@InputAction.Score /></div>

	<text class="h1">Helpful Tips</text>
	<text>Do not instantly trust loud accusations. Ask where a player was, what weapon they heard, and who confirmed the body.</text>
	<text>Traitors win more rounds by looking helpful than by sprinting for early kills.</text>
	<text>Detectives are high-value targets, so staying alive is often more important than forcing a risky duel.</text>
</root>

<style>
	HelpPage {
		flex-direction: column;
		justify-content: flex-start;
		overflow: scroll;
		width: 100%;
		color: white;
		flex-shrink: 0;
		font-size: 16px;
		gap: 8px;

		.h1 {
			color: white;
			font-weight: bold;
			margin-top: 10px;
		}

		div {
			align-items: center;
			flex-shrink: 0;
		}

		inputglyph,
		text {
			flex-shrink: 0;
			margin-right: 10px;
		}
	}
</style>
